The paper deals with time synchronization attacks on the GPS system, which is a critical infrastructure for many applications. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a technique for estimating clock bias and drift, which is related to network synchronization and time estimation, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely sub-category. The proposed technique also involves correcting the clock bias and drift in real-time, which is related to control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible sub-category. The paper also involves mathematical modeling and estimation, which is related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a technique that can be easily implemented in off-the-shelf receivers, which is related to software engineering, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) another possible sub-category.
